				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The iNES spec calls it "vertical mirroring", and I guess emulators just follow that. But most of Nintendo's discrete boards (NROM, C*ROM, U*ROM, B*ROM) have "H" and "V" solder pads for horizontal arrangement and vertical arrangement of the nametables, which is opposite the convention that the iNES spec uses.
<br />
<br />As for calling horizontal arrangement "horizontal scrolling", the scrolling direction is independent of the nametable. Super Mario Bros. 3 uses vertical arrangement (horizontal mirroring) in the vast majority of levels, but you don't see any vertical scrolling at all in 1-2, or in 1-1 until Mario gets the tail.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

